                            <comment id="15993127" author="ijuma" created="Tue, 2 May 2017 15:43:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There are 2 changes here. One is to use AdminClient, which doesn&apos;t require a KIP. The second is to update KafkaClientSupplier to include a method for the AdminClient. That does require a tiny KIP. We may do both at the same time, but it&apos;s not strictly required.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16046560" author="wlsc" created="Mon, 12 Jun 2017 13:32:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Will be it addressed in 0.11.0.0 release?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16046763" author="guozhang" created="Mon, 12 Jun 2017 16:47:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think it will not be included in the 0.11.0 release as there is no progress on it yet.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=sharad.develop&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;sharad.develop&quot;&gt;sharad.develop&lt;/a&gt; are you still actively working on this ticket?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16052858" author="sharad.develop" created="Sat, 17 Jun 2017 14:37:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes,I guess I was waiting for the KIP to get created.  Is that been created?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16054904" author="mjsax" created="Mon, 19 Jun 2017 22:51:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Doing the KIP is part of the JIRA, so it&apos;s your call to do it &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; Sorry if this was not clear. Please have a look at &lt;a href=&quot;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/KAFKA/Kafka+Improvement+Proposals&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/KAFKA/Kafka+Improvement+Proposals&lt;/a&gt; Let us know if you need any help.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, as we did not do the switch to &lt;tt&gt;AdminClient&lt;/tt&gt; yet, I would recommend to defer this JIRA until this internal change was done. Otherwise, we need to update &lt;tt&gt;KafkaClientSupplier&lt;/tt&gt; twice.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16057227" author="enothereska" created="Wed, 21 Jun 2017 09:19:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mjsax&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mjsax&quot;&gt;mjsax&lt;/a&gt; I don&apos;t understand your last comment about &quot;we did not switch to AdminClient yet&quot;. Could you please elaborate? I was under the impression that this JIRA is the one that at a minimum does the switch (by replacing StreamsKafkaClient with AdminClient) and optionally does a KIP (to extend KafkaClientSupplier). &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16057257" author="ijuma" created="Wed, 21 Jun 2017 09:43:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I suggest doing 2 separate JIRAs: one for the implementation swap and another for the public API change.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16057259" author="enothereska" created="Wed, 21 Jun 2017 09:45:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sounds good. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=sharad.develop&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;sharad.develop&quot;&gt;sharad.develop&lt;/a&gt; which one would you like to do? I&apos;ll then do the other one (unless you want to do both). &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16057842" author="mjsax" created="Wed, 21 Jun 2017 16:56:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I meant was Ismael said. This Jira as intended to add a public API to &lt;tt&gt;KafkaClientSupplier&lt;/tt&gt; to allow returning the &lt;tt&gt;AdmitClient&lt;/tt&gt;. It requires that we do have the &lt;tt&gt;AdminClient&lt;/tt&gt; in place internally first. Btw: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=guozhang&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;guozhang&quot;&gt;guozhang&lt;/a&gt; mentioned to me, that he might want to work on the internal swap. We should create a JIRA for this and link both to each other with this JIRA being blocked by the other.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16057853" author="sharad.develop" created="Wed, 21 Jun 2017 17:08:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mjsax&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mjsax&quot;&gt;mjsax&lt;/a&gt; Thanks for the clarification.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=enothereska&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;enothereska&quot;&gt;enothereska&lt;/a&gt; I will stick to doing this one only.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16250209" author="guozhang" created="Mon, 13 Nov 2017 20:44:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We have &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-6170&quot; title=&quot;Add the AdminClient in Streams&amp;#39; KafkaClientSupplier&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-6170&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-6170&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for the KIP-related changes to add AdminClient to public API KafkaClientSupplier. Modified the title / description of this ticket for internal implementation only.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
